(33, 1, '2018-01-05 15:29:33', '2018-01-05 15:29:33', '<section id="bg_general" class="sub_header"></section><!-- End Section-->\r\n<div id="position">\r\n    <div class="container">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>\r\n            <li>About</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div><!-- End Position-->\r\n<div class="container margin_60">\r\n    <div class="main_title"><span></span>\r\n        <h2>Downham Hall</h2>\r\n        <p class="lead">Downham Hall is the former home of the de Beauvoir family and the house has had many\r\n            incarnations and now we are hoping to let others enjoy it with us as accommodation for guests.</p></div>\r\n    <div class="row"><p> We are based in a wonderful location only 30-40 minutes from Central London and in lovely\r\n            countryside.\r\n            Feels as though you are far from the hustle and bustle of the City but 5 minutes from many rail links and\r\n            close to many major roads.\r\n            We have listed many activities to do in the area but strolling about the local area is a great place to\r\n            start.\r\n            We are now converting the Hall bit by bit ready to take guests this summer in the North Wing and\r\n            hopefully</p>\r\n        <div class="col-md-8">\r\n            <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6"><img src="https://www.downhamhall.com/wp-content/themes/animatedone/img/about_1.jpg"\r\n                                                    alt="Richard Benyon De Beauvoir"\r\n                                                    class="img-responsive styled">\r\n                    <h3>Full of history</h3>\r\n                    <p>Records indicate there has been a property on the site since the 1500s with various incarnations\r\n                        since. The currnet property is believed to be from the 1700s with an extension in the early\r\n                        1900s. It was most notably the home of<strong>&nbsp;de Beauvoir family</strong> who built a\r\n                        large part of East London, particularly around Hackney. The Hall was also the farm house\r\n                        previously and connected to the adjoining farm until the last century.</p></div>\r\n                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6"><img src="https://www.downhamhall.com/wp-content/themes/animatedone/img/about_2.jpg"\r\n                                                    alt=""\r\n                                                    class="img-responsive styled">\r\n                    <h3>Country setting</h3>\r\n                    <p>Just 1 mile from Wickford and close to Billericay too you would never realise considering the\r\n                        fields on all sides. We have reinvigorated the gardens to ensure<strong>&nbsp;stunning views of\r\n                            the fields</strong> and the chance to see the countryside bear witness to birds of prey,\r\n                        deer and many other types of wildlife is great for all but in particular children. Our children\r\n                        were born in London and are captivated by the new environment.</p></div>\r\n                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6"><img src="https://www.downhamhall.com/wp-content/themes/animatedone/img/about_3.jpg"\r\n                                                    alt=""\r\n                                                    class="img-responsive styled">\r\n                    <h3>Enjoy and relax</h3>\r\n                    <p>We have a huge fireplace as you enter the North Wing and we are sure you will relax as soon as\r\n                        you turn up the drive and take your first look at where we are. With so much to do in the\r\n                        area<strong>&nbsp;you can\'t help but to enjoy</strong> your time in this much overlooked part of\r\n                        the UK.</p></div>\r\n                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6"><img src="https://www.downhamhall.com/wp-content/themes/animatedone/img/about_4.jpg"\r\n                                                    alt=""\r\n                                                    class="img-responsive styled">\r\n                    <h3>Close to civilisation</h3>\r\n                    <p>Major trainlines into London Liverpool Street and London Fenchurch Street mean you can easily get\r\n                        to us or into town. We are close to Wickford, Billericay and Chelmsford.<strong>&nbsp;Shopping\r\n                            is nearby</strong> as we have Lakeside and Freeport Shopping areas close too. Many good\r\n                        quality food places are also easily reachable and we can help with advice on where might suit\r\n                        you best.</p></div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="col-md-4">\r\n            <ul id="about" class="feat">\r\n                <li><i class="icon_set_1_icon-86"></i><h4>Free wifi</h4>\r\n                    <p>Our rooms have access to the free wifi and in time we will roll out provision to the whole\r\n                        property to use the internet service.</p></li>\r\n                <li><i class="icon_set_2_icon-110"></i><h4>Swimming pool</h4>\r\n                    <p>We have an outside swimming pool available and heated in the summer months. This is currently\r\n                        being renovated and will be ready later in the year.</p></li>\r\n                <li><i class="icon_set_1_icon-3"></i><h4>Family Friendly</h4>\r\n                    <p>Downham Hall is run by a young family and we are happy to entertain families and can provide toys\r\n                        and other items to families as needed. Phone ahead with any questions and we will do our best to\r\n                        help as much as we can.</p></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div><!-- End Row-->\r\n    <hr><!--#testimonials--><!--  .row--><!--    .col-md-