(34, 1, '2018-01-05 15:31:51', '2018-01-05 15:31:51', '<section id="bg_general" class="sub_header"></section><!-- End Section-->\r\n<div id="position">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href="/">Home</a></li>\r\n 	<li>About</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- End Position-->\r\n<div class="container margin_60">\r\n<div class="main_title">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Downham Hall</h2>\r\n<p class="lead">Downham Hall is the former home of the de Beauvoir family and the house has had many incarnations and now we are hoping to let others enjoy it with us as accommodation for guests.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\nWe are based in a wonderful location only 30-40 minutes from Central London and in lovely countryside.\r\nFeels as though you are far from the hustle and bustle of the City but 5 minutes from many rail links and close to many major roads.\r\nWe have listed many activities to do in the area but strolling about the local area is a great place to start.\r\nWe are now converting the Hall bit by bit ready to take guests this summer in the North Wing and hopefully\r\n<div class="col-md-8">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6">\r\n\r\n<img class="img-responsive styled" src="https://www.downhamhall.com/wp-content/themes/animatedone/img/about_1.jpg" alt="Richard Benyon De Beauvoir" />\r\n<h3>Full of history</h3>\r\nRecords indicate there has been a property on the site since the 1500s with various incarnations\r\nsince. The currnet property is believed to be from the 1700s with an extension in the early\r\n1900s. It was most notably the home of<strong> de Beauvoir family</strong> who built a\r\nlarge part of East London, particularly around Hackney. The Hall was also the farm house\r\npreviously and connected to the adjoining farm until the last century.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6">\r\n\r\n<img class="img-responsive styled" src="https://www.downhamhall.com/wp-content/themes/animatedone/img/about_2.jpg" alt